        <article class="settings-panel">
          <div class="panel-header">
            <div class="panel-kicker">Guardrails</div>
            <h2 class="panel-title">Keeping automation safe</h2>
            <p class="panel-desc">Credentials are only as safe as the habits around them.</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="guardrails-list">
            <li>Keep production route-write access separate from read-only metrics keys so observation does not imply mutation.</li>
            <li>Assign one key per automation workflow so revocation does not force unrelated systems to rotate at the same time.</li>
            <li>Prefer region-specific tokens during staged rollouts to limit the blast radius of misrouted deploy jobs.</li>
            <li>After a manual hotfix or operator override, rotate the key involved and record why the extra privilege was needed.</li>
          </ul>
